                <path
                  d="M13 14.725c0-5.141 3.892-10.519 10-11.725l.984 2.126c-2.215.835-4.163 3.742-4.38 5.746 2.491.392 4.396 2.547 4.396 5.149 0 3.182-2.584 4.979-5.199 4.979-3.015 0-5.801-2.305-5.801-6.275zm-13 0c0-5.141 3.892-10.519 10-11.725l.984 2.126c-2.215.835-4.163 3.742-4.38 5.746 2.491.392 4.396 2.547 4.396 5.149 0 3.182-2.584 4.979-5.199 4.979-3.015 0-5.801-2.305-5.801-6.275z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-6 text-[var(--text)] italic">
            "Compliance requirements around production data has always required
            significant internal tool development for my previous engineering
            teams. It was a lot of effort that still felt subpar and left
            engineers feeling handcuffed when trying to solve data issues in
            production. Once we implemented QueryDesk, within a day, our teams
            gained access to production data with valid controls and seamless
            ability to restrict and redact controlled data. It was a lifesaver.
            We also gained enhanced team metrics that helped uncover bottlenecks
            in our team processes. Code coverage reporting was another plus. The
            entire suite of tools were a big win with very little implementation
            effort."
          </p>
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-[var(--text)]">Kyle K.</p>
            <p class="text-[var(--text-light)] text-sm">CEO, Stealth Startup</p>
          </div>
        </div>

